definition: far/distant/remote/(intensifier in a comparison) by far/much (lower etc)
the implied message is deep (idiom); having deep implications

sentences.english: Once Synechococcus spp. forms bloom, its influence will be far-reaching to whole ecosystem.
sentences.chinese: 一旦形成赤潮，对整个生态系统的影响将非常深远。

sentences.english: Confucius' thought and theory of later generations produced profound influence.
sentences.chinese: 孔子地思惟及学说对后世发生啦极端深远地影响。

sentences.english: The construction of high-speed railway in city will have profound influence on the city development.
sentences.chinese: 高速铁路市区段的建设对城市的发展将产生深远影响。

sentences.english: The Chinese version of Sutras translation has a far-reaching influence on Chinese classical poetry.
sentences.chinese: 汉译佛经对中国古典诗歌有着非常深远的影响。

sentences.english: He also had a profound influence on 19th century European impressionists .
sentences.chinese: 他对19世纪时欧洲印象派也产生了深远影响。

sentences.english: Liu Guozheng's Chinese life view has a far-reaching impact on new course of Chinese.
sentences.chinese: 刘国正语文生活观对语文新课程产生深远的影响。

sentences.english: They look like the sunset as vast and far-reaching, let me feel heavy.
sentences.chinese: 他们的眼神像落日一样苍茫而深远，让我觉得沉重。

sentences.english: In addition, foreign investors have been attracted by these far-reaching reforms.
sentences.chinese: 此外，这些具有深远意义的改革还吸引着外国投资者。

sentences.english: Both of them have deep relations with the "Nuo"dance in ancient times.
sentences.chinese: 它们与古傩都有着深远的源流关系。

sentences.english: Zhou Yang has a profound effect on the new Chinese literature theory textbooks.
sentences.chinese: 周扬对新中国文学理论教材影响深远。

sentences.english: So we can say that the Qing emperor's character policy has a profound significance to the afterworld.
sentences.chinese: 秦始皇的文字政策对后世有着深远意义。

sentences.english: Such an earthshaking change must have far-reaching effects.
sentences.chinese: 像这样翻天覆地的变化一定会产生深远的影响。

sentences.english: In a word, Song-Confucianism exerts a far-reaching influence on Song Dynasty aesthetics.
sentences.chinese: 综上所述，宋代理学对宋代美学产生的影响是深远的。

sentences.english: This had a far-reaching effects on pattern of US-Soviet Cold War and the situation in the Middle East.
sentences.chinese: 这对美苏冷战格局和中东局势都产生了深远影响。

sentences.english: The early 80’s was a seminal time in computing history.
sentences.chinese: 上世纪80年代初是计算机发展史上影响深远的时代。

sentences.english: This combined thesis has been Frege’s most enduring legacy to the philosophy oflanguage.
sentences.chinese: 这一思想成为弗雷格对语言哲学影响最深远的遗产。

definition: deep/profound/(of a person) reserved/undemonstrative/(of a voice, sound etc) deep/low-pitched
out of the ordinary/unusually (good, talented etc)
thought-provoking/worth thinking over/to provide food for thought
